Models tested for predicting MHP-solvent binding energy : LASSO, Ridge Regression, Support Vector Regressor, XGBoost Regressor, Gaussian Process Regressor, Random Forest

Dataset used : 'datasets/MHP_bandgaps_AND_perov_solvent_BE/nestedae_dataset/perov_bandgaps_PBE_arun_reduced.csv'

descriptors = ['A_IONRAD',
               'A_MASS',
               'A_DPM',
               'B_IONRAD',
               'B_MASS',
               'B_EA',
               'B_IE',
               'B_En',
               'B_AN',
               'X_IONRAD',
               'X_MASS',
               'X_EA',
               'X_IE',
               'X_En',
               'X_AN'
]
target = ['Gap']

Best performing model parameters 
found through

grid = GridSearchCV(estimator=XGBRegressor(random_state=random_state),
                    param_grid=param_grid_xgb,
                    scoring='neg_mean_absolute_error', 
                    cv=split_idxs_all_folds, # If using None defaults to 5 fold cross-validation
                    n_jobs=-1, 
                    verbose=1,
                    return_train_score=True)

-----------------------------------------------------------------

XGBoost:

param_grid_xgb = {
        'n_estimators': [250, 500, 1000, 2000],
        'learning_rate': [0.01, 0.05, 0.1],
        'max_depth': [2, 3, 4, 5],
        'subsample': [0.4, 0.6, 0.8, 1.0],
    }

Best performing model = {'learning_rate': 0.01, 'max_depth': 5, 'n_estimators': 2000, 'subsample': 0.4}

-----------------------------------------------------------------

Random Forest Regressor :

param_grid_RF = {
    'n_estimators': [100, 200, 500, 1000],
    'max_depth': [2, 3, 4, 5, 10],
    'ccp_alpha': [0.0, 0.01, 0.1]
}

Best performing model = {'ccp_alpha': 0.0, 'max_depth': 10, 'n_estimators': 500}

-----------------------------------------------------------------

Nu Support Vector Regression :

param_grid_nusvr = {
    'nu': [0.25, 0.5, 0.75],
    'kernel': ['rbf', 'linear', 'poly', 'sigmoid'],
    'degree': [2, 3, 4],  # Only relevant for 'poly' kernel
    'coef0': [0.0, 0.1, 0.5],  # Only relevant for 'poly' and 'sigmoid' kernels
    'C': [0.5, 1, 5, 10, 50, 100]
}

Best performing model = {'C': 5, 'coef0': 0.5, 'degree': 3, 'kernel': 'poly', 'nu': 0.75}

------------------------------------------------------------------

LASSO :

param_grid_lasso = {
        'alpha':[0.0001, 0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 1.0]
}

Best performing model = {'alpha': 0.0001}

-----------------------------------------------------------------

Ridge Regression : 

param_grid_ridge = {
          'alpha':[0.0001, 0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 1.0]
}

Best performing model = {'alpha': 0.1}

 
